SIMPLE: incurvation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incurvation
<hw>In`cur*va"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incurvatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>incurvation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of bending, or curving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being bent or curved;
curvature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>incurvation</qex> of the rays.</q>
<rj><qau>Derham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act of bowing, or bending the body, in respect
or reverence.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>incurvations</xex> of the
knee.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incurve</ent>⟦br⟧
